Chart 1: Map

This map attempts to display the geographic spread of the data by placing a marker at each city mentioned in the data set.

As can be seen from the graph, the cities with the highest median house prices in September 2017 (the last available date from the data) are largely clustered around large coastal metropolis areas such as Seattle, New York, and Los Angeles.

Chart Number 2

This bar plot takes the average of the given median house prices at the beginning of each year to illustrate annual changes in house price This bar graph shows how prices have dropped from 2010 to 2012. And prices have risen from 2012 to 2017. Prices were slightly higher in 2017 than in 2010, indicating a general trend that house prices increase.
